				<div class="beebom-single-content entry-content highlight">
											<div class="beebom-single-thumbnail">
							<img width="1168" height="657" src="fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-Zlatan-in-Career-Mode.webp" class="attachment-beebom-single-thumbnail size-beebom-single-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="Zlatan shooting in EA FC 26" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-Zlatan-in-Career-Mode_003.webp 1200w, fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-Zlatan-in-Career-Mode_004.webp 300w, fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-Zlatan-in-Career-Mode_005.webp 768w, fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-Zlatan-in-Career-Mode_002.webp 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1168px) 100vw, 1168px">							<div class="beebom-single-thumbnail-caption">
								Image Credit: EA Sports							</div>
						</div>
										<!-- Article New Updates Highlighter List -->
																				<div class="beebom-single-content-container">
						
<p>EA FC 26 is the latest addition in the long-running football sim 
franchise, and just like its predecessor, it’s available on PC via 
Steam, Epic Games Store, and EA Play. Recent entries in the series have 
performed quite poorly on PCs, with EA FC 25 being the worst offender. 
Maximising performance in these games requires plenty of optimization in
 the settings menu, and we’re here to save you from all that tinkering. 
On that note, here are the best EA FC 26 PC settings for high FPS and 
stable performance. </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-best-ea-fc-26-pc-settings">Best EA FC 26 PC Settings</h2>



<figure class="wp-block-image size-large"><img decoding="async" height="576" width="1024" src="fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-PC-Settings-Menu_002.webp" alt="EA FC 26 PC Settings Menu" class="wp-image-994851" srcset="fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-PC-Settings-Menu_005.webp 1200w, fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-PC-Settings-Menu_003.webp 300w, fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-PC-Settings-Menu.webp 768w, fifa%2026%201_soubory/EA-FC-26-PC-Settings-Menu_004.webp 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px"><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Image Credit: EA Sports/EA FC 26 (screenshot by Aryan Singh/Beebom)</figcaption></figure>



<!-- More Money --><div class="text-center content-ad" style="min-height: 280px;"><!-- Tag ID: beebom_incontent_1_AdSense --><div align="center" data-beebom-freestar-identifier="beebom_incontent_1_AdSense" name="beebom_incontent_1_AdSense_replacement" data-freestar-ad="__336x280 __336x280" id="beebom_incontent_1_AdSense" data-google-query-id="CMKWrNCMpJEDFUfAjgkd9vowXg"><div id="google_ads_iframe_/15184186,52315147/5839_beebom_incontent_1_AdSense_0__container__" style="border: 0pt; display: inline-block; width: 468px; height: 280px;"><iframe frameborder="0" style="border: 0px; vertical-align: bottom;" src="fifa%2026%201_soubory/container.htm" id="google_ads_iframe_/15184186,52315147/5839_beebom_incontent_1_AdSense_0" title="3rd party ad content" name="" scrolling="no" marginwidth="0" marginheight="0" width="468" height="280" data-is-safeframe="true" sandbox="allow-forms allow-popups allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox allow-same-origin allow-scripts allow-top-navigation-by-user-activation" aria-label="Advertisement" tabindex="0" data-google-container-id="7" data-load-complete="true"></iframe></div></div></div><p>The EA FC 26 PC settings listed below should deliver smooth performance on hardware that aligns with the <a href="https://beebom.com/ea-fc-26-system-requirements/">recommended system requirements</a>. So, if you’re rig is in the same ballpark as the hardware EA recommends, try out these settings: </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-display-settings">Display Settings</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Screen Resolution</strong>: 1920 x 1080/Based on Monitor</li>



<li><strong>Frame Rate Limit</strong>: 144 FPS</li>



<li><strong>VSync</strong>: Off</li>



<li><strong>Cutscene Performance</strong>: Full Frame Rate</li>



<li><strong>Render Scale</strong>: 100</li>



<li><strong>Dynamic Resolution Scaling</strong>: Off</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-graphics-settings">Graphics Settings</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Graphic Preset</strong>: Custom</li>



<li><strong>Rendering Quality</strong>: Medium</li>



<li><strong>Strand-Based Hair</strong>: Off</li>



<li><strong>Grass Quality:</strong> Medium</li>



<li><strong>Crowd Quality</strong>: Medium</li>



<li><strong>Cloth Quality</strong>: Medium</li>



<li><strong>Ambient Occlusion Quality</strong>: Medium</li>



<li><strong>Motion Blur</strong>: Off</li>
</ul>



<p>These settings prioritize performance and smooth gameplay above all 
else. We’ve kept every visual option at Medium and turned off 
Strand-Based Hair to cut down on needless GPU usage. You’ll still be 
getting some gorgeous on-pitch action, but not without sacrificing 
frames, whether it’s in Career Mode or Ultimate Team. </p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-best-ea-fc-26-settings-for-low-end-pcs">Best EA FC 26 Settings for Low-End PCs</h2>



<p>According to FC 26’s system requirements sheet, the game should 
technically run on a GPU as outdated as the GTX 1050 Ti. In practice, 
things just aren’t this simple since you’re bound to run into micro 
stutters and inconsistent frametimes. To help fix those issues, make 
sure to use the PC settings listed below: </p>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-display-settings-0">Display Settings</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Screen Resolution</strong>: 1920 x 1080</li>



<li><strong>Frame Rate Limit</strong>: 90 FPS</li>



<li><strong>VSync</strong>: Off</li>



<li><strong>Cutscene Performance</strong>: Full Frame Rate</li>



<li><strong>Render Scale</strong>: 100</li>



<li><strong>Dynamic Resolution Scaling</strong>: On</li>



<li><strong>Dynamic Resolution FPS Target</strong>: 90 FPS</li>
</ul>



<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="h-graphics-settings-0">Graphics Settings</h3>



<ul class="wp-block-list">
<li><strong>Graphic Preset</strong>: Custom</li>



<li><strong>Rendering Quality</strong>: Low</li>



<li><strong>Strand-Based Hair</strong>: Off</li>



<li><strong>Grass Quality:</strong> Low</li>



<li><strong>Crowd Quality</strong>: Low</li>



<li><strong>Cloth Quality</strong>: Low</li>



<li><strong>Ambient Occlusion Quality</strong>: Medium</li>



<li><strong>Motion Blur</strong>: Off</li>
</ul>



<p>If you’re on the lower end of the hardware spectrum, then these 
settings should deliver consistent performance in EA FC 26. While it’s a
 shame that the title does not support Nvidia DLSS or AMD FSR, its 
in-built upscaling technique does a decent job at improving the 
framerate. Enable the DRS option and turn down almost every visual 
setting, bar Ambient Occlusion, and you should see a stable 60 FPS.</p>



<p>And that wraps up our guide on the best PC settings to use in EA FC 
26. Let us know if you’re facing any performance troubles in the 
comments. </p>



